lefdefInputCheckColoredShape(25.10)        lefdefInputCheckColoredShape(25.10)

Name
       lefdefInputCheckColoredShape

Syntax
        lefdefInputCheckColoredShape { true | false}

       Type: Boolean

       Default: false

       Specifies  to check and ignore colored shapes on colorless layers while
       reading the LEF or DEF data. When set to true, the tool errors out if a
       colored shape is on a colorless layer. When set   to  false,  the  tool
       gives an error message and ignores the color.

